# MuseHub Architecture

Follow the project layers:

- `src/app`: app assembly, route contracts, navigation, global config.
- `src/pages`: route-level page modules and page contracts.
- `src/widgets`: large page regions composed from features and entities.
- `src/features`: user actions and interactive workflows.
- `src/entities`: domain models and entity data contracts.
- `src/shared`: reusable UI, contracts, primitives, and utilities.
- `src/styles`: global CSS, HeroUI styles, tokens, and responsive rules.

Dependency direction must stay one-way:

`app` -> `pages/widgets/features/entities/shared`

`pages` -> `widgets/features/entities/shared`

`widgets` -> `features/entities/shared`

`features` -> `entities/shared`

`entities` -> `shared`

`shared` must not import higher layers.

Do not implement planned pages until requested. For preparatory work, add contracts, registry entries, types, docs, or empty module boundaries only.

Keep routing declarations in `src/app/routing/route-paths.ts`, page metadata in `src/pages/*/contract.ts`, and navigation in `src/app/navigation/primary-navigation.ts`.

Before adding a new dependency, verify the existing stack cannot solve the problem. HeroUI v3, React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, and local CSS are the default frontend toolkit.
